body:
In Verilator 5, when using `--protect-lib`, some signal names and source locations are leaked in the generated lib (**debug version only**). For example, when building [t_timing_pong.v](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/blob/master/test_regress/t/t_timing_pong.v) with `--protect-lib` we get in the resulting C++:
```cpp
        co_await vlSelf->PSjiBj.trigger("@([event] t.ping)", "t_timing_pong.v", 13);
```
```cpp
        co_await vlSelf->PSPfrs.trigger("@([event] t.pong)", "t_timing_pong.v", 21);
```
```cpp
    co_await vlSelf->PS42o9.delay(1U, "t_timing_pong.v", 28);
```
```cpp
    co_await vlSelf->PS42o9.delay(2U, "t_timing_pong.v", 29);
```
```cpp
    co_await vlSelf->PS42o9.delay(3U, "t_timing_pong.v", 34);
```
```cpp
    if (vlSelf->PSGxwc.at(0U)) {
        VL_DBG_MSGF("         'act' region trigger index 0 is active: @([event] t.ping)\n");
    }
    if (vlSelf->PSGxwc.at(1U)) {
        VL_DBG_MSGF("         'act' region trigger index 1 is active: @([event] t.pong)\n");
    }
    if (vlSelf->PSGxwc.at(2U)) {
        VL_DBG_MSGF("         'act' region trigger index 2 is active: @([true] __VdlySched.awaitingCurrentTime())\n");
    }
```
```cpp
    if ((1U & (~ (IData)(vlSelf->PSlsB3.any())))) {
        VL_DBG_MSGF("         No triggers active\n");
    }
    if (vlSelf->PSlsB3.at(0U)) {
        VL_DBG_MSGF("         'nba' region trigger index 0 is active: @([event] t.ping)\n");
    }
    if (vlSelf->PSlsB3.at(1U)) {
        VL_DBG_MSGF("         'nba' region trigger index 1 is active: @([event] t.pong)\n");
    }
    if (vlSelf->PSlsB3.at(2U)) {
        VL_DBG_MSGF("         'nba' region trigger index 2 is active: @([true] __VdlySched.awaitingCurrentTime())\n");
    } 
```

